item.title: How do i get this example C:/demo_cache_32/
item.dc:creator: @Mendorphins Mendorphins
item.description:
@Mendorphins wrote:

Check your signlink.java for the directory of the cache (./cacheName means it’s in the folder of the client), providing you know how to rename a folder… do that to the cache folder, move the folder to your C:/ drive and then change the directory in your signlink.java.

If it doesn’t work there could possibly be another “findCacheDir2()” method or whatever that overrides the first one.
